comment: Represents information about a piece of media (for example, an audio or video file).

variables.name: SOURCE_TYPE_UNSPECIFIED
variables.comment: The media item's source is not known.

variables.name: SOURCE_TYPE_GALLERY
variables.comment: The media item came from the device gallery.

variables.name: SOURCE_TYPE_CAMERA
variables.comment: The media item came directly from camera capture.

variables.name: SOURCE_TYPE_EDITING_SESSION
variables.comment: The media item was output by a previous editing session.

variables.name: SOURCE_TYPE_LOCAL_FILE
variables.comment: The media item is stored on the local device's file system.

variables.name: SOURCE_TYPE_REMOTE_FILE
variables.comment: The media item is a remote file (for example, it's loaded from an HTTP server).

variables.name: SOURCE_TYPE_REMOTE_LIVE_STREAM
variables.comment: The media item is a remotely-served live stream.

variables.name: SOURCE_TYPE_GENERATED
variables.comment: The media item was generated by another system.

variables.name: DATA_TYPE_IMAGE
variables.comment: The media item includes image data.

variables.name: DATA_TYPE_VIDEO
variables.comment: The media item includes video data.

variables.name: DATA_TYPE_AUDIO
variables.comment: The media item includes audio data.

variables.name: DATA_TYPE_METADATA
variables.comment:
* The media item includes static media container metadata (for example, capture frame rate or
     * location information).

variables.name: DATA_TYPE_DEPTH
variables.comment: The media item includes depth (z-distance) information.

variables.name: DATA_TYPE_GAIN_MAP
variables.comment: The media item includes gain map information (for example, an Ultra HDR gain map).

variables.name: DATA_TYPE_HIGH_FRAME_RATE
variables.comment: The media item includes high frame rate video data.

variables.name: DATA_TYPE_SPEED_SETTING_CUE_POINTS
variables.comment:
* The media item includes time-dependent speed information (for example, slow motion cue
     * points).

variables.name: DATA_TYPE_GAPLESS
variables.comment: The media item includes gapless audio metadata.

variables.name: DATA_TYPE_SPATIAL_AUDIO
variables.comment: The media item includes spatial audio data.

variables.name: DATA_TYPE_HIGH_DYNAMIC_RANGE_VIDEO
variables.comment: The media item includes high dynamic range (HDR) video.

variables.name: VALUE_UNSPECIFIED
variables.comment: Special value for numerical fields where the value was not specified.

methods.name: public int getSourceType()
methods.comment: * Returns where the media item came from, or {@link #SOURCE_TYPE_UNSPECIFIED} if not specified.

methods.name: public long getDataTypes()
methods.comment: Returns the data types that are present in the media item.

methods.name: public long getDurationMillis()
methods.comment:
* Returns the duration of the media item, in milliseconds, or {@link #VALUE_UNSPECIFIED} if not
     * specified.

methods.name: public long getClipDurationMillis()
methods.comment:
* Returns the duration of the clip taken from the media item, in milliseconds, or {@link
     * #VALUE_UNSPECIFIED} if not specified.

methods.name: public String getContainerMimeType()
methods.comment: Returns the MIME type of the media container, or {@code null} if unspecified.

methods.name: public List<String> getSampleMimeTypes()
methods.comment:
* Returns the MIME types of samples stored in the media container, or an empty list if not
     * known.

methods.name: public List<String> getCodecNames()
methods.comment:
* Returns the {@linkplain MediaCodec#getName() media codec names} for codecs that were used as
     * part of encoding/decoding this media item, or an empty list if not known or not applicable.

methods.name: public int getAudioSampleRateHz()
methods.comment: * Returns the sample rate of audio, in Hertz, or {@link #VALUE_UNSPECIFIED} if not specified.

methods.name: public int getAudioChannelCount()
methods.comment: Returns the number of audio channels, or {@link #VALUE_UNSPECIFIED} if not specified.

methods.name: public long getAudioSampleCount()
methods.comment:
* Returns the number of audio frames in the item, after clipping (if applicable), or {@link
     * #VALUE_UNSPECIFIED} if not specified.

methods.name: public Size getVideoSize()
methods.comment:
* Returns the video size, in pixels, or a {@link Size} with width and height set to {@link
     * #VALUE_UNSPECIFIED} if not specified.

methods.name: public int getVideoDataSpace()
methods.comment: Returns the {@linkplain DataSpace data space} for video, as a packed integer.

methods.name: public float getVideoFrameRate()
methods.comment:
* Returns the average video frame rate, in frames per second, or {@link #VALUE_UNSPECIFIED} if
     * not specified.

methods.name: public long getVideoSampleCount()
methods.comment:
* Returns the number of video frames, aftrer clipping (if applicable), or {@link
     * #VALUE_UNSPECIFIED} if not specified.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)

methodNames: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)
